13.3.20 Secrets Home Services
-----------------------------

The ‘(gnu home services secrets)’ module provides services pertaining to
storing secrets, notably including password managers.

Himitsu Services
................

Himitsu (https://himitsustore.org/) is a daemon for storing arbitrary
secrets encrypted by a single password.  The daemon operates alongside a
prompter, which asks the user for permission when an application
requests a secret, and for the store password on first use in a session.
Neither Himitsu nor its underlying cryptography library have been
indepednently audited.

 -- Variable: home-himitsu-service-type
     This service provides the main Himitsu store daemon.  It will not
     launch unless you have a store set up - run ‘himitsu-store -i’
     after the service is added to your profile to create it, and then
     ‘herd start himitsud’ to restart the service.  Configuration is as
     follows:

 -- Data Type: home-himitsu-configuration
     ‘package’ (default: ‘himitsu’)
          Package to find ‘himitsud’ in.

     ‘notify-reuse’ (optional)
          Interpreted shell command to run on application access to an
          already-approved secret.

     ‘prompter’ (default: ‘(wrap-himitsu-prompter (file-append hiprompt-gtk "/bin/hiprompt-gtk"))’)
          Path to a prompter binary.  Defaults to ‘hiprompt-gtk’, the
          reference implementation.  If your prompter is graphical, you
          should pass it through the provided ‘wrap-himitsu-prompter’
          procedure, which will autodetect a running display to prompt
          on, due to the Himitsu daemon starting before the display
          server is online.

     ‘extra-options’ (optional)
          List of extra strings or G-expressions to insert verbatim into
          the Himitsu configuration file.  Each list element gets its
          own line.

   Himitsu can be used through its command-line tool ‘hiq’ or through
any number of supporting services, providing compatability to other
applications.  Git credential support may be provided simply by adding
the ‘himitsu-git’ package to your profile, but other such supporting
services are listed below:

 -- Variable: home-himitsu-ssh-service-type
     This service provides an ‘ssh-agent’ implementation that stores
     keys through Himitsu.  You may interact with a running daemon
     through ‘hissh-import’ and ‘hissh-export’.

 -- Data Type: home-himitsu-ssh-configuration
     ‘package’ (default: ‘himitsu-ssh’)
          Package to find ‘hissh-agent’ in.

     ‘persist’ (default: ‘'(session 300 refuse)’)
          List of options given when prompting to allow this service
          access to your list of keys.  The option chosen decides how
          long ‘himitsu-ssh’ has this access.  Options can be either
          ‘'session’ (access is retained until the daemon closes),
          ‘'refuse’ (access is declined and the prompter will not ask
          again), ‘'skip’ (ask again next use), or a numerical access
          timeout in seconds.

     ‘disclose’ (default: ‘'(skip session 300)’)
          List of options given when prompting to allow this service use
          of your secret keys.  Has the same format as ‘persist’.

 -- Variable: home-himitsu-secret-service-type
     This service provides a freedesktop Secret Service
     (https://specifications.freedesktop.org/secret-service/latest/)
     implementation, allowing Himitsu to replace *note
     gnome-keyring-service-type: Desktop Services. and *note
     kwallet-service-type: Desktop Services.

 -- Data Type: home-himitsu-secret-service-configuration
     ‘package’ (default: ‘himitsu-secret-service’)
          Package to find ‘hisecrets-agent’ in.


